# UI Sanity Check Before Done

Do not mark a UI task complete until sibling controls on the same row/section look consistent.

## Required Before Close-Out

When adding or changing buttons, toggles, fields, or toolbar items on a page that already has a visual language:

1. Read the nearest existing control in the same toolbar/row/modal.
2. Reuse the same shell: height, border radius, border color, padding, label typography, min-width.
3. Prefer the page's existing `sx` preset/box shell over raw MUI `Button`/`TextField` defaults.
4. Verify in browser or screenshot at desktop width before reporting done.

## Staff Schedule Table Toolbar Preset

Controls in the table toolbar row must match:

- Shell: 44px min-height, 18px radius, `#E5E5E5` border, white background, 240px min-width on desktop
- Label: 14px, weight 500, `#666666`, line-height 1.25
- Layout: same outlined field shell as `Календарь` / `Цветовые обозначения`

Do not use MUI `Button` defaults in that row unless typography and height visibly match the switch fields.

## Fail Conditions

- Label font clearly larger/smaller than siblings
- Different control height or corner radius in the same toolbar
- New control uses theme defaults while neighbors use custom shells
- Reporting "done" without checking parity against adjacent UI
